    {
      "name": "Auth 🔒",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Iniciar sesión",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\r\n    \"username\": \"chabelo\",\r\n    \"password\": \"pepe\"\r\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "http://localhost:8080/api/auth/login",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": [
                "localhost"
              ],
              "port": "8080",
              "path": [
                "api",
                "auth",
                "login"
              ]
            },
            "description": "## Endpoint Login\n\nSe usará para autenticar un usuario para darle acceso a los demás funciones.\n\n### Request\n\n- **Method:** `POST`\n    \n- **Endpoint:** `http://localhost:8080/api/auth/login`\n    \n- **Request Body:** The request must contain a JSON payload with the following parameters:\n    \n    - `username` (string): The username of the user attempting to log in.\n        \n    - `password` (string): The password associated with the provided username.\n        \n\n### Example Request Body\n\n``` json\n{\n  \"username\": \"your_username\",\n  \"password\": \"your_password\"\n}\n\n ```\n\n### Response\n\n- **Status Code:** `401 Unauthorized` indicates that the authentication has failed.\n    \n- **Content-Type:** `text/xml`\n    \n\n### Expected Response Format\n\nThe response will be in XML format, indicating the failure of the authentication attempt. The content will not contain any specific details about the failure.\n\n### Note\n\nEnsure that the credentials provided in the request body are correct to avoid receiving a `401 Unauthorized` response."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
